<FILEID>AP-NR-11-16-89 0045EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r a AM-TyronePowerRemembered     11-16 0150</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Tyrone Power Remembered,0152</SECOND>
<HEAD>Mourners Remember Actor 31 Years After His Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Marine Corps honor guard and a crowd of 45
mourners paid homage to the late actor Tyrone Power on Wednesday,
the 31st anniversary of his death.
   ``His presence has been very significant in my life,'' said
Taryn Power, one of the late actor's two daughters, who was among
those gathered at Hollywood Memorial Park Cemetery. The crowd
``always amazes me,'' she added.
   The Marine guard honored Power's World War II service.
   Power, star of such films as ``Witness for the Prosecution,''
``The Razor's Edge'' and ``Captain from Castille,'' died of a heart
attack at the age of 45. He collapsed on a movie set in Spain in
1958.
   Three thousand people mobbed the cemetery when he was buried in
a white marble tomb, and there has been an annual memorial ever
since.
</TEXT>
