<SECOND>PM-BRF--Unseen Body,0136</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Lies Dead in Hospital Bathroom for Five Days</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The body of a 61-year-old man lay undiscovered for
at least five days in a toilet cubicle at a top London hospital,
the hospital said.
   A cleaner found the body of William Frost on Tuesday afternoon
in a busy outpatients' bathroom at St. Bartholomew's Hospital,
operational manager Ian Johnson said Wednesday.
   Frost died ``five or six days'' ago, and the results of an
autopsy Wednesday were not immediately available, Johnson said.
Frost was at the hospital for an X-ray but apparently died before
he was examined, Johnson said.
   The hospital has begun an investigation into how their cleaners
operate, and an inquiry into the circumstances of Frost's death is
being carried out by the local health authority, Johnson said.
