<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Germany-Gas     11-16 0142</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Germany-Gas,0145</SECOND>
<HEAD>Gas Running Short as East Germans Prepare Another Weekend in West</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-East Germany, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GERA, East Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   So many people are filling up their
tanks in preparation for shopping trips to West Germany that the
Gera district near the inter-German border is running out of gas.
   Taxis have disappeared for lack of gasoline. The local newspaper
Volkswacht complained that some people had bought up to 42 gallons,
filling up cars as well as extra containers for refills on the road.
   The newspaper said it was proving impossible to keep up with
demand, despite the use of tankers belonging to the army and the
police.
   About 3 million East Germans visited West Berlin and West
Germany last weekend, taking advantage of their new travel freedom.
That many or more are expected to cross the border this weekend.
</TEXT>
