<FILEID>AP-NR-11-16-89 1447EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f AM-SteelImports     11-16 0187</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Steel Imports,0195</SECOND>
<HEAD>Imports Down In September</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steel imports in September decreased 8.6
percent from August and were down 18.6 percent for the first nine
months of the year, an industry group said Thursday.
   Steel imports in September totaled 1.4 million tons, compared
with 1.5 million tons in August and 1.6 million tons in September
1988, the American Iron and Steel Institute reported.
   Imports for the first nine months of the year fell to 13 million
tons, compared with 16 million tons in the same period last year,
the Washington, D.C.-based trade group said.
   The American Institute for Imported Steel, which represents
leading steel importers and exporters, said imports for the first
nine months amounted to 15.3 percent of domestic demand when
semifinished steel bound for U.S. mills is excluded.
   The steel import group noted the percentage without semifinished
steel is below the Bush administration's Voluntary Restraint
Agreements target of 18.5 percent of imported steel in the domestic
market.
   Steel exports in September totaled 363,849, down 21.1 percent
from August, the importers' group said. In September 1988, American
steel manufacturers exported 206,760 tons.
</TEXT>
