<FIRST>r f BC-ChampionLayoffs     11-16 0114</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Champion Layoffs,0119</SECOND>
<HEAD>Champion Lays Off 166 At Hamilton Paper Mill</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HAMILTON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Champion International Corp. said Thursday
it will lay off 166 workers at the paper maker's printing and
writing paper mill.
   J. Douglas Banks, Champion's operations manager at the plant,
said in a statement that the layoffs were needed to help the mill
compete in a difficult worldwide market for premium papers.
   The plant previously employed 1,845 people, Banks said. He said
154 hourly employees were laid off and 12 salaried workers lost
their jobs.
   Banks said Champion would negotiate severance payments with
union leaders for the hourly workers and would offer to help
salaried employees find new jobs.
