<SECOND>BC-Auto Prodn,0154</SECOND>
<HEAD>Production Goes Down This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
208,756 cars and light trucks this week, down from last week's
209,208, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago,
in which 254,869 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade
journal said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 136,066 cars this week,
compared with 133,936 a week ago and 163,245 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 72,690,
compared with last week's 75,272 and last year's 91,624.
   Canadian automakers were to build 21,476 cars this week, down
from 26,147 a week ago and up from last year's 17,737.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 19,449,
compared with 16,168 a week ago and 22,218 in the same week last
year.
</TEXT>
